18726.name: {YE{yndles{Ys S{yan{Yd D{yune{Ys{x
description: {WY{yo{Yu are in the barren desert of Athas:  nothing but endless stretches of glistening
{Ws{ya{Ynd as far as the eye can see, blazing hot to the touch as it bakes under the
{Ws{ye{Yemingly ever-present sun.  Only scarce plant life, and even less critter life
{Ws{yc{Yatters these wastes, for the harshness of the desert allows only the most hardy
{Wc{yr{Yeatures the ability to survive.  What few life happens to be present here is
{Ws{yu{Yrely dangerous and more likely than not, unfriendly.. as only the strong survive
{Wh{ye{Yre while the weak.. perish.{x

18814.name: {C({YT{yyr{C){x - {WD{wesert Gate{Ws{x
description: The city of Tyr lies stretched out northwards, the vast desert of Athas looming through the other
end of the city's metal gates.  The city itself appears to be in shambles;  the stone from which
the surrounding walls and even the buildings are crafted from is crumbling and stripped of paint.
The street below you, made from perhaps the same stone, is in disrepair as well.  To the west, a
gaping window allows sight into one of the dilapidated buildings.

18670.name: {GE{gndles{Gs {YS{yan{Yd {GD{gune{Gs{x
description: {GT{gh{Yere is a slight change in the bleak landscape in this area.  The sand is not
{Gq{gu{Yite as hot here.. it is harder as well.  Small bits of green are poking through
{Gt{gh{Ye darker-shaded areas of sand.  The further west you travel, the more abundant
{Gt{gh{Yis growth becomes.  This could certainly mean only one thing.. water is near-by.
{GW{gi{Yth water, perhaps, comes food.  The hope of survival lies to the west.  The
{Gp{gr{Yomise of death, every other direction.{x

end of the city's metal gates.  The city itself appears to be in shambles;  the stone from which
the surrounding walls and even the buildings are crafted from is crumbling and stripped of paint.
The street below you, made from perhaps the same stone, is in disrepair as well.  One single guard
mans the gate, he is wearing minimal armor and does not look overly interested in his job.
